- It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Boston Scientific in Arden Hills, MN and A.K or residence. The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, social media including but not limited to texting, Facebook, Twitter, contact through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

If the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bail jumping.

10:15 AM Apprs: CO: S. Needham, Rpr: V. Kasten, Clerk: B Harris, Defendant Robert T. Cesena in court.  Attorney Aaron A. Nelson in court for Robert T. Cesena.  Prosecuting attorney Holly Elkin Rockow in court for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews file.  Atty Nelson states there is an agreement to a Deferred Judgment of Conviction, an Amended Information has been filed. ADA Rockow agrees.  Court reads charge and maximum penalty.  DE pleads NC to AMENDED Ct 1- Criminal Trespass to Dwelling, NC to AMENDED Ct 2- Disorderly Conduct and NC to AMENDED Ct 3- Disorderly Conduct in 22CF160.  DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights.  Atty Nelson states there is a discrepancy on the new amended information in regards to the date range.  ADA Rockow will file a new amended information with correct dates. Court modifies the amount of contacts that DE is to have with the diversion program. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea.  Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of the 3 AMENDED counts in 22CF160.   Court withholds sentence in favor of DJOC on all 3 counts.  Diversion Program to provide quarterly updates regarding DE's compliance. Adjourned at 10:34 AM. bph
